CloudSim is a simulation toolkit used to model and simulate cloud computing environments. It
helps in analyzing resource allocation, scheduling algorithms, and performance without using real
cloud infrastructure.

Procedure
1. Install Java (JDK 1.8).
2. Set Java environment variables.
3. Download and install Eclipse IDE.
4. Download CloudSim package and extract it.
5. Download required jar files (commons-math3).
6. Add all jar files to Eclipse project.
7. Create a new Java project.
8. Create a new class inside src folder.
9. Write CloudSim simulation program.
10. Run the program in Eclipse.

